	   <tr><td colspan=2>Monk by Default.<br><br>Why do Monks always say they should get good light weight armor? <br><br>1)&nbsp;&nbsp;THEY PULL - lets see a warrior try to pull without a cleric on /autofollow.  Hail, wipe.<br><br>2)  Monk armor is GARBAGE -   Golden Star Chest Wraps - 23ac | Warlords BP - 59ac drop off the same mobs,  over DOUBLE, that's fair.<br><br>3) These legs are 1ac, 5sta 50hp more than Warlords.  Go tank a mob that hits for 1000, and you tell me if 1ac 5sta 50hp is going to do jack squat?<br><br>This item should go to the class who will benefit from them the most.  Which is monks, everyone else gets far better equipment.  Another curse of the &quot;Vision&quot;.<br>The second best legs for monks, are 25ac. 2 weight.<br><br>Warriors, when a Monk gets this.  Press your I button, and look at your 45 AC legs you got from farming West ToV mobs (Monk's Kael legs 11ac goodgame.), and your 59AC BP.  Then say Grats Monk. Thanks.<br><br>&nbsp;<br>Merquise Tranquil<br>Master -&nbsp;&nbsp;Rodcet Nife</td></tr>
