	   <tr><td colspan=2>The very stats on these legs instantly rule out a few classes: Cleric, Druid and Shaman. They have no need for these legs as they are missing more vital components such as +mana +wis or +resists, ac is nice, but not that important to a Priest to give them this item.<br><br>Below is a list taken right from Allakhazam of the Leggings available to all classes, sorted by AC (no limiting factor):<br><br>If you look at all the other classes who can use this (excluding the priests) they all have a viable alternative to the Acient Wurm Hide Greaves. If your at the level to be arguing over who to give this item to, then you should also be capable of getting the equivalent item for other classes.<br><br>These greaves give 21 more ac than the next best bit of equipment a monk could have, second inline is the Rogue or the Ranger where the biggest difference (excluding the Onyx Chain Leggings) is 14.<br><br>There are very few good AC greaves for a monk, and these are perfectly suited - they have all the vital stats except for resists, 0 weight, 50hp, 10sta and 46ac - not to mention they are tiny so they could fit in the small bags monks are forced to carry should they wish to swap them out.<br><br>It looks pretty obvious that when Verant made these legs they have a class in mind, the monk. The facts show that these leggings are made best use of by a monk.<br><br>I personally play a druid and have never played a monk but if it was for me to decide then these would go to any monks in the guild.<br><br>Monk: Ancient Wurm Hide Greaves&nbsp;&nbsp;+46 AC +10 Sta +15 vsFire +50 HP 0.00 Wt<br>Monk: Ancient Wyvern Hide Leggings  +25 AC +5 Str +15 Sta +25 Agi +15 vsDis +50 HP +2.00 Wt<br>Monk: Oiled Greaves  +15 AC +7 Str +20 HP +5 Mana +1.50 Wt<br><br>Warrior: Warlord's Greaves  +45 AC +9 Str +5 Sta +7 Dex +5 vsMg +5 vsFire +8.50 Wt<br>Warrior: Greaves of the Deep Sea  +44 AC +55 HP +2.50 Wt<br><br>Rogue: Onyx Chain Leggings  +45 AC +10 Str +10 